description._content:
Second page of a printed constitution for the Women Citizens' League of Deseronto, Ontario.

"Women Citizens' League
Constitution
Title:
The name of this Association shall be the 'Women Citizens' League'
Officers:
The officers shall be a President, four Vice-Presidents, a Secretary, and a Treasurer.
Cabinet:
The President and Vice-Presidents shall form a Cabinet.
Quorum:
Seven members shall constitute a quorum.
Fees:
The membership fee shall be one dollar per year payable in advance.
Status:
This association shall be non-political and non-sectarian, and membership shall be open to all women of the town.
Meetings:
The annual meeting shall be held on the third Thursday of each year."

One of a number of items which originally belonged to Cecil and Elizabeth Argue of Deseronto, Ontario. Donated to the Archives in October 2013.
